{"article_id":"LhS51AzW7urSYCNl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Democrats Reject Trump Border Wall Proposal ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Calling It A 'Non-Starter '","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"With negotiations","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"over reopening the government","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"at a standstill ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"President Trump offered to back temporary protections for some immigrants","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"brought to the country illegally as children ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"many of whom are now adults ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"in exchange for funding for a wall on the Southern border .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"In a White House speech on Saturday , Trump also offered to extend the Temporary Protected Status program","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that blocks deportation of certain immigrants","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"fleeing civil unrest or natural disasters .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"$ 805 million for drug-detection technology","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"to secure ports of entry ; 75 new immigration judge teams for a court backlog of nearly 900,000 cases ;","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"Allowing Central American minors to apply for asylum in their home countries ;","depth":14},{"id":15,"text":"$ 5.7 billion for strategic deployment of physical barriers , or a wall , but not ,","depth":16},{"id":16,"text":"Trump said ,","depth":16},{"id":17,"text":"a 2,000-mile concrete structure .","depth":15},{"id":18,"text":"The president said","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"he wants to add 230 miles this year","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"and claimed","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"the crime rate and drug problem `` would be quickly and greatly reduced ''","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"and that `` some say","depth":15},{"id":23,"text":"it would be cut in half . ''","depth":15},{"id":24,"text":"Three years of legislative relief for some 700,000 recipients of the Obama-era initiative","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"known as Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals , or DACA ,","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"which protects some immigrants","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"brought to the U.S. illegally as children from deportation .","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"The Trump administration had moved to end DACA ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"but the decision was challenged in court","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"and is currently held up in legal proceedings .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Trump 's proposal would give an extension of legal status ;","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"A three-year extension of Temporary Protected Status for some 300,000","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"facing expiration ;","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"The president said","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"these measures would allow three more years of certainty","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"to work on a larger immigration deal .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"However ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"even before he spoke ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"the deal appeared to be dead on arrival with Democratic leaders .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"They insisted","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Trump needs to open the government","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"before beginning any negotiations over border security or barrier funding .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"Before the speech , House Speaker Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , responded to initial reports of the president 's offer","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"by calling it `` a compilation of several previously rejected initiatives ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"each of which is unacceptable . ''","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"She added","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"that Trump 's proposal does not `` represent a good faith effort","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"to restore certainty to people 's lives . ''","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"Some 800,000 federal workers throughout the country have either been furloughed","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"or made to work","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"without pay .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Workers have now missed one paycheck","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"and will miss another","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"if the shutdown is not resolved in the next week .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Trump has signed legislation","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"to give back pay to federal workers","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"once the government is reopened .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , pledged to put Trump 's proposal up for a vote this week .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"`` Everyone has made their point","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"- now it 's time","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"to make a law , ''","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"McConnell said in a statement shortly after the speech .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"`` I intend to move to this legislation this week .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"With bipartisan cooperation , the Senate can send a bill to the House quickly","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"so that they can take action as well .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"The situation for furloughed employees is n't getting any brighter","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"and the crisis at the border is n't improved by show votes .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"But the president 's plan is a path","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"toward addressing both issues quickly . ''","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Rep. Mark Meadows , R-N.C. , head of the conservative House Freedom Caucus , praised Trump 's move","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"and put the ball in Democrats ' court .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"But not everyone in the conservative base was happy with Trump 's proposal .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Conservative commentator Ann Coulter called Trump 's move `` amnestying millions of illegals . ''","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"During this , the longest partial government shutdown in U.S. history , Trump has suffered in the polls ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"which have found more people blame the president than congressional Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"And that number is on the rise .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"An NPR/PBS NewsHour/Marist poll also found Trump 's approval rating down to 39 percent","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"and slipping with his base .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"Coming out Saturday","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"and making this speech","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"was an attempt by the president","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"to reclaim the narrative","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"and appear conciliatory .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"Democrats indicate","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"the president did not reach out to them before the speech","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"and do n't see what he 's doing ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"as Pelosi noted ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"as a good faith effort at compromise .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Trump 's offer is based , in part , on bipartisan legislation","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"proposed by Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , and Dick Durbin , D-Ill. ,","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"known as the Bridge Act .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"The bill would give three years of protections to the so-called `` DREAMers ''","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"- immigrants","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"who came to the U.S. illegally as children .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"But before Trump 's speech , Durbin , a member of the Democratic leadership in the Senate , rejected Trump 's use of the bill in this way","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"and called","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"for the government first to be reopened","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"before any negotiations on a border barrier could take place .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"`` First , President Trump and Senate Majority Leader McConnell must open the government today , ''","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"said Durbin , the minority whip in the Senate .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"`` Second , I can not support the proposed offer","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"as reported","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"and do not believe","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"it can pass the Senate .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Third , I am ready to sit down at any time","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"after the government is opened","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"and work","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"to resolve all outstanding issues . ''","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"This is the latest move by the White House in the midst of its showdown with Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"who have balked at providing the money for construction of a border wall .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Democrats contend","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that Trump 's push for the wall is immoral","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"and that it is an ineffective way","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"to stop illegal crossings .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"Trump argues","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"a wall is necessary for national security .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"He has refused to sign any spending bill","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"without funding for it .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"Back in December , the president indicated","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"that he would sign temporary funding measures","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"to keep the government open","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"but then faced a backlash in conservative media over it .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"He reversed course ,","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"which led to the shutdown .","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"Until now , the White House had said","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"it would be open to negotiating on the amount of money","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"it will accept for a wall","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"but has been noncommittal about offering other concessions to Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"Almost a year ago , Democrats offered some $ 25 billion in exchange for a path to citizenship for those almost 700,000 DACA recipients .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Democrats say","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"Trump balked at the offer ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"demanding more","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"after Democrats thought","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"they had a deal .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"Democrats have passed several bills out of the House","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"to fund and reopen agencies","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"that are currently shut down .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"McConnell has not brought them to the floor of the Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"deferring instead to the need for negotiations between Trump and Democrats .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":279,"left":141,"right":278,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":217,"right":277,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":187,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":181,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":175,"right":180,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":147,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":143,"right":146,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":143,"left":142,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":142,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":5,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":149,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":9,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":170,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":167,"right":169,"r